And in fact, just one
final note about-- what

00:38:28.620 --> 00:38:30.890
is it that is coming?

00:38:30.890 --> 00:38:33.304
We all have DNA, we
all understand DNA.

00:38:33.304 --> 00:38:34.470
It's the be all and end all.

00:38:34.470 --> 00:38:36.790
It turns out, in a
computer context that's

00:38:36.790 --> 00:38:38.570
like the operating system.

00:38:38.570 --> 00:38:40.440
It virtually never changes.

00:38:40.440 --> 00:38:43.610
It's the most boring
part of our biology.

00:38:43.610 --> 00:38:47.000
In fact, we have four genomes
that we're all born with.

00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:50.100
And one keeps us alive,
keeps us reproducing.

00:38:50.100 --> 00:38:51.430
That's our DNA.

00:38:51.430 --> 00:38:54.130
We're all 99.9%
identical, otherwise

00:38:54.130 --> 00:38:56.120
we wouldn't survive
as a species.

00:38:56.120 --> 00:39:00.070
The other two are your epigenome
which is switches on your DNA

00:39:00.070 --> 00:39:01.340
that get flipped.

00:39:01.340 --> 00:39:03.210
This is what happens
when the famine comes.

00:39:03.210 --> 00:39:04.900
This is what happens when
the violence changes,

00:39:04.900 --> 00:39:06.450
when the weather
comes, when you're

00:39:06.450 --> 00:39:09.790
deprived of love as a child, why
does it turn to heart disease

00:39:09.790 --> 00:39:10.852
when you're 80?

00:39:10.852 --> 00:39:12.560
These are these switches
getting flipped.

00:39:12.560 --> 00:39:14.680
That's a very important genome.

00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:17.730
And the epigenetic code
has not been uncovered.

00:39:17.730 --> 00:39:20.807
And that's like having
programs like Word or Microsoft

00:39:20.807 --> 00:39:22.390
or, you know, any
of the applications.

00:39:22.390 --> 00:39:24.420
The next one is your
microbes in your body.

00:39:24.420 --> 00:39:25.950
We're now finding
microbes that are

00:39:25.950 --> 00:39:27.980
providing 30 percent
of the nutrients

00:39:27.980 --> 00:39:29.550
and toxins in our body.

00:39:29.550 --> 00:39:31.250
Every day we are
carrying these around.

00:39:31.250 --> 00:39:34.040
They've changed completely
in the last 50 years because

00:39:34.040 --> 00:39:36.090
of antibiotics, because
of the food we eat,

00:39:36.090 --> 00:39:37.820
we are totally
engineering the microbes.

00:39:37.820 --> 00:39:39.110
This is like little apps.

00:39:39.110 --> 00:39:41.500
They're actually sitting
on top of our genome,

00:39:41.500 --> 00:39:43.510
changing little
applications every day.

00:39:43.510 --> 00:39:45.930
And they will be engineered
into functional foods

00:39:45.930 --> 00:39:47.190
in the next decade.

00:39:47.190 --> 00:39:49.770
And finally there's
viruses that live in us.

00:39:49.770 --> 00:39:51.710
At the DNA level
they're 10-fold more

00:39:51.710 --> 00:39:54.890
abundant than bacteria, which
are 10-fold more abundant

00:39:54.890 --> 00:39:56.380
than our human cells.

00:39:56.380 --> 00:39:58.820
This is the dark matter
of humanity right now.

00:39:58.820 --> 00:40:01.427
These viruses that live in
us, we do not understand.

00:40:01.427 --> 00:40:03.010
They're driving our
evolution, they're

00:40:03.010 --> 00:40:05.710
driving our nature every day,
and there's more to come.

00:40:05.710 --> 00:40:08.440
But what I can say is, if you
have a healthy, happy life

00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:10.000
and follow the
basic rules that you

00:40:10.000 --> 00:40:11.772
hear every week
from your doctor,

00:40:11.772 --> 00:40:13.480
things are going to
work out pretty well.

00:40:13.480 --> 00:40:16.075
And with that I'll say,
thank you very much.

00:40:16.075 --> 00:40:17.751
I hope you read our book.

