be green, tiny, and poisonous.

00:41:04.950 --> 00:41:07.010
Potatoes used to be poisonous.

00:41:07.010 --> 00:41:10.840
So what we've been doing
for a long period of time

00:41:10.840 --> 00:41:13.424
is to evolve things
to our purposes

00:41:13.424 --> 00:41:14.840
and select things
to our purposes.

00:41:14.840 --> 00:41:16.700
Now, what we've
been doing lately

00:41:16.700 --> 00:41:21.650
is we've been doing things that
are, I think, far more extreme.

00:41:21.650 --> 00:41:23.750
On the one hand you
could say, well, humans

00:41:23.750 --> 00:41:26.570
are just a evolutionary system
and they're a natural outgrowth

00:41:26.570 --> 00:41:28.710
of an evolutionary system.

00:41:28.710 --> 00:41:31.000
Yeah, but I think
it's important to make

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:33.180
a distinction between
what we're doing,

00:41:33.180 --> 00:41:34.680
how we're engineering
stuff, and how

00:41:34.680 --> 00:41:36.550
things worked in Darwin's time.

00:41:36.550 --> 00:41:39.529
Because if you don't do that,
then what ends up happening

00:41:39.529 --> 00:41:41.820
is you don't take responsibility
for what you're doing.

00:41:41.820 --> 00:41:44.150
You kind of say, you know,
this stuff just happens.

00:41:44.150 --> 00:41:46.440
It's all natural, que sera sera.

00:41:46.440 --> 00:41:48.200
And it's not que
sera sera, right?

00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:54.420
It's, I choose to do this at
this point to this species.

00:41:54.420 --> 00:41:56.310
And that has real consequences.

00:41:56.310 --> 00:41:59.530
And if we want to continue
to have the power we have

00:41:59.530 --> 00:42:01.090
and continue to
deploy it, we better

00:42:01.090 --> 00:42:04.015
recognize that this is a
break point in evolution.

00:42:04.015 --> 00:42:05.765
STEVE GULLANS: And
we're just following up

00:42:05.765 --> 00:42:06.598
on what Darwin said.

00:42:06.598 --> 00:42:09.780
He attributed natural selection
that anything was effectively

00:42:09.780 --> 00:42:10.990
not driven by humans.

00:42:10.990 --> 00:42:14.290
He used terms like artificial
selection, human selection,

00:42:14.290 --> 00:42:15.892
because he understood
animal breeding.

00:42:15.892 --> 00:42:17.100
He understood plant breeding.

00:42:17.100 --> 00:42:19.190
But he said these are
two different worlds.

00:42:19.190 --> 00:42:21.390
And from his perspective,
150 years ago,

00:42:21.390 --> 00:42:24.080
nature will always win.

00:42:24.080 --> 00:42:26.718
That's what we think
is in debate now.

00:42:26.718 --> 00:42:29.375
AUDIENCE: I guess I can't
get a sense of whether or not

00:42:29.375 --> 00:42:31.458
